WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:03.655 --> 00:00:06.093
Job came in about
an hour ago from sanitation.

2
00:00:06.136 --> 00:00:08.051
There was nothing else?
Just the head?

3
00:00:08.095 --> 00:00:11.620
So far. M.E.'s office
is on the way.

4
00:00:11.663 --> 00:00:13.230
Pretty decomposed.

5
00:00:13.274 --> 00:00:16.016
Why don't you go on up there
and have a closer look?

6
00:00:16.059 --> 00:00:18.235
He just said M.E.'s on the way.

7
00:00:18.279 --> 00:00:20.672
I'll look out for them. Go on.

8
00:00:26.113 --> 00:00:27.679
When you were taking the test.

9
00:00:27.723 --> 00:00:29.855
you ever think you'd be
climbing up a pile of garbage

10
00:00:29.899 --> 00:00:31.466
to get to a severed head?

11
00:00:31.509 --> 00:00:33.772
No. Thought I'd be more like

12
00:00:33.816 --> 00:00:37.211
Paul Newman
in Fort Apache. The Bronx.

13
00:00:37.254 --> 00:00:39.082
It was Cagney & Laceyfor me.

14
00:00:39.126 --> 00:00:41.084
You know we could just retire.

15
00:00:41.128 --> 00:00:43.652
and go to a tropical island
and solve crimes there.

16
00:00:43.695 --> 00:00:45.001
We could. but you would

17
00:00:45.045 --> 00:00:46.655
never survive outside
the five boroughs.

18
00:00:46.698 --> 00:00:48.265
That's true.

19
00:00:50.572 --> 00:00:51.834
Yeah. it's Mano Sangriento.

20
00:00:51.877 --> 00:00:53.227
Black hand?

21
00:00:53.270 --> 00:00:56.230
No. just the fingers.
But it was a hand.

22
00:00:56.273 --> 00:00:57.753
That's the calling card.

23
00:00:57.796 --> 00:00:59.165
Yeah. Now we're gonna
have to figure out

24
00:00:59.189 --> 00:01:01.496
why this guy lost his head.

25
00:01:01.539 --> 00:01:05.195
Jose Cortez. 30.
from Sunset Park.

26
00:01:05.239 --> 00:01:08.242
Cops found him in possession
of a half-ounce of cocaine.

27
00:01:08.285 --> 00:01:10.635
Criminal possession
in the third degree.

28
00:01:10.679 --> 00:01:12.333
But Cortez has no priors.
so he's eligible

29
00:01:12.376 --> 00:01:13.856
for judicial diversion.

30
00:01:13.899 --> 00:01:17.164
So he'll get drug treatment
instead of jail time.

31
00:01:17.207 --> 00:01:19.316
And Schneiderman is on deck. so
no doubt she'll recommend rehab.

32
00:01:19.340 --> 00:01:21.144
You run a triple I check
to make sure he doesn't have

33
00:01:21.168 --> 00:01:22.517
a record outside of New York?

34
00:01:22.560 --> 00:01:25.215
His record's clean.
Legal aid's gonna ask for R.O.R.

35
00:01:25.259 --> 00:01:26.825
What do you want to do?

36
00:01:26.869 --> 00:01:28.305
I'll ask for 500 bail.

37
00:01:28.349 --> 00:01:29.698
She'll R.O.R. him anyway.

38
00:01:29.741 --> 00:01:31.265
And so it goes.

39
00:01:31.308 --> 00:01:32.764
All right. well. you seem to
have everything under control.

40
00:01:32.788 --> 00:01:33.963
You need anything from me?

41
00:01:34.006 --> 00:01:35.007
A raise.

42
00:01:35.051 --> 00:01:37.401
Get in line.

43
00:01:41.449 --> 00:01:43.407
You want some breakfast?

44
00:01:43.451 --> 00:01:46.236
Kale and protein powder?
I think I'll pass.

45
00:01:46.280 --> 00:01:47.561
If you show me what's under
that robe. I'll make you

46
00:01:47.585 --> 00:01:49.152
whatever you want. Well. in that case.

47
00:01:49.196 --> 00:01:52.155
you're gonna have to produce
some pretty killer pancakes.

48
00:01:56.116 --> 00:01:57.900
Wish I didn't have court.

49
00:01:57.943 --> 00:02:01.295
It's better than being stuck
in Jersey traffic.

50
00:02:01.338 --> 00:02:03.166
No. I mean. I wish
I could come with you.

51
00:02:03.210 --> 00:02:04.733
It's no biggie.

52
00:02:04.776 --> 00:02:06.493
Telling your mom that
we're engaged is a biggie.

53
00:02:06.517 --> 00:02:08.215
Plus. I haven't
even met her yet.

54
00:02:08.258 --> 00:02:10.565
Exactly. Let's keep it that way.

55
00:02:10.608 --> 00:02:11.653
What does that mean?

56
00:02:11.696 --> 00:02:15.178
My mother has scared off

57
00:02:15.222 --> 00:02:17.702
every boyfriend
I've ever introduced her to.

58
00:02:17.746 --> 00:02:19.748
I'm not every boyfriend.

59
00:02:19.791 --> 00:02:22.577
Well. then you'll see
for yourself when you meet her.

60
00:02:22.620 --> 00:02:24.013
At the wedding.

61
00:02:25.275 --> 00:02:27.321
Ridiculous.

62
00:02:30.280 --> 00:02:32.480
Eddie. great news. My court date
got pushed to tomorrow.

63
00:02:33.762 --> 00:02:36.025
I can come with you. Wait. what?

64
00:02:36.068 --> 00:02:38.070
Yeah. I'll just take the
day and come with you.

65
00:02:38.114 --> 00:02:40.334
No. definitely not.

66
00:02:43.380 --> 00:02:46.296
Invisibility.
Definitely invisibility.

67
00:02:46.340 --> 00:02:48.516
No. man. Spidey-sense.

68
00:02:48.559 --> 00:02:51.083
Then. you get fair warning
when something's gonna go down.

69
00:02:51.127 --> 00:02:53.216
How about X-ray vision?

70
00:02:53.260 --> 00:02:56.132
No. There are things
I don't want to see.

71
00:02:56.176 --> 00:02:59.222
I've always had a thing
for the Lasso of Truth.

72
00:02:59.266 --> 00:03:02.312
Come in handy when
we make detective.

73
00:03:10.929 --> 00:03:12.888
Hey. why do you guys
always weigh the brain?

74
00:03:12.931 --> 00:03:14.281
To see how much they weigh.

75
00:03:14.324 --> 00:03:17.327
Actually. it's to look
for abnormalities.

76
00:03:17.371 --> 00:03:18.676
This one is

77
00:03:18.720 --> 00:03:20.243
three pounds
of memories. emotions

78
00:03:20.287 --> 00:03:22.767
and 86 billion nerve cells.

79
00:03:22.811 --> 00:03:25.770
I've always wondered about the
part that controls your emotion.

80
00:03:25.814 --> 00:03:27.250
The amygdala.

81
00:03:27.294 --> 00:03:29.252
Kind of wish I could have it
removed sometimes.

82
00:03:29.296 --> 00:03:30.751
Yeah. but then you'd
be a serial killer.

83
00:03:30.775 --> 00:03:31.950
What can you tell us about

84
00:03:31.994 --> 00:03:33.493
the head you found
at the garbage dump?

85
00:03:33.517 --> 00:03:36.390
I'm waiting on DNA. but the time
of death and the injuries

86
00:03:36.433 --> 00:03:38.392
are consistent
with that headless corpse

87
00:03:38.435 --> 00:03:40.220
you guys brought me
a few weeks ago.

88
00:03:40.263 --> 00:03:42.265
You mean the one belonging
to Luis Delgado?

89
00:03:42.309 --> 00:03:44.572
That body wasn't Luis Delgado.

90
00:03:44.615 --> 00:03:46.182
What are you talking about?

91
00:03:46.226 --> 00:03:48.924
That body and the head that
you pulled out from the garbage

92
00:03:48.967 --> 00:03:51.013
this morning appear
to belong to the same person.

93
00:03:51.056 --> 00:03:52.580
No. the body
we found on the beach

94
00:03:52.623 --> 00:03:55.670
with Luis Delgado's clothes on
and Luis Delgado's tattoos

95
00:03:55.713 --> 00:03:57.367
belong to Luis Delgado.

96
00:03:57.411 --> 00:03:58.803
Trust me.

97
00:03:58.847 --> 00:04:01.371
I had to get dental records
from Mexico to confirm.

98
00:04:01.415 --> 00:04:03.721
Great. Then the son of a bitch

99
00:04:03.765 --> 00:04:06.507
who burned down my house
is still alive.

100
00:04:08.000 --> 00:04:14.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

101
00:04:18.606 --> 00:04:20.477
What is it?

102
00:04:20.521 --> 00:04:24.002
Two officers sitting
on a witness's house

103
00:04:24.046 --> 00:04:26.701
were shot multiple times
inside their patrol car.

104
00:04:26.744 --> 00:04:28.093
Both critical.

105
00:04:28.137 --> 00:04:30.618
Anyone likely? Information's
still coming in.

106
00:04:30.661 --> 00:04:32.750
They're at Saint Irene's.

107
00:04:32.794 --> 00:04:34.230
And the shooter?

108
00:04:34.274 --> 00:04:35.362
No word yet.

109
00:04:35.405 --> 00:04:38.365
Frank. one of the officers

110
00:04:38.408 --> 00:04:41.193
is Abigail's husband.

111
00:05:24.454 --> 00:05:25.977
Hey.

112
00:05:26.021 --> 00:05:27.544
Two cops were shot
in their patrol car.

113
00:05:27.588 --> 00:05:29.372
I heard. Any word
on their condition?

114
00:05:29.416 --> 00:05:31.374
Still waiting. But Erin.

115
00:05:31.418 --> 00:05:33.811
they just picked up the shooter.

116
00:05:33.855 --> 00:05:35.857
It's Jose Cortez.

117
00:05:37.902 --> 00:05:39.295
The guy we released
this morning?

118
00:05:39.339 --> 00:05:41.341
He went straight from
arraignment court

119
00:05:41.384 --> 00:05:44.039
to his apartment.
he picked up a .45

120
00:05:44.082 --> 00:05:47.303
and he opened fire. He's got
a record for murder and assault.

121
00:05:47.347 --> 00:05:49.610
No. His rap sheet came up empty.

122
00:05:49.653 --> 00:05:51.176
It came up empty in our system

123
00:05:51.220 --> 00:05:53.701
because his priors
were in Mexico.

124
00:05:53.744 --> 00:05:56.486
Anthony. this is my fault.

125
00:05:56.530 --> 00:05:57.922
No.

126
00:05:57.966 --> 00:06:00.272
Your A.D.A. followed
the bail recommendations

127
00:06:00.316 --> 00:06:01.273
to the letter.

128
00:06:01.317 --> 00:06:02.536
Tell that to the two cops

129
00:06:02.579 --> 00:06:04.364
laying in the hospital.

130
00:06:43.315 --> 00:06:45.317
Officer Davis is out of surgery.

131
00:06:45.361 --> 00:06:47.232
He's in recovery.

132
00:06:47.276 --> 00:06:49.626
Brian took a bullet to his neck.

133
00:06:49.670 --> 00:06:51.628
which severed his jugular.

134
00:06:55.893 --> 00:06:58.635
Did I ever show you
Brian's department photo?

135
00:07:06.382 --> 00:07:09.429
You're not supposed to.
but... he smiled.

136
00:07:09.472 --> 00:07:11.822
On purpose.

137
00:07:11.866 --> 00:07:14.346
He said every time
you see a cop shot

138
00:07:14.390 --> 00:07:16.000
on the front page of the paper.

139
00:07:16.044 --> 00:07:19.439
it's always the official photo
and they look so serious.

140
00:07:19.482 --> 00:07:22.006
He figured if he smiled.
it was...

141
00:07:22.050 --> 00:07:25.445
some sort of guarantee that
nothing bad would happen to him.

142
00:07:28.883 --> 00:07:32.190
He might be right.

143
00:07:32.234 --> 00:07:36.456
I've promised him all kinds
of things if he gets better.

144
00:07:56.084 --> 00:07:57.868
Brian.

145
00:07:57.912 --> 00:08:01.306
it's Commissioner Reagan.

146
00:08:21.631 --> 00:08:24.504
Whatever it takes. Abigail.

147
00:08:29.596 --> 00:08:30.945
I'm telling you.

148
00:08:30.988 --> 00:08:33.208
Delgado had this guy
made up to look like him.

149
00:08:33.251 --> 00:08:34.601
even down to the tattoo.

150
00:08:34.644 --> 00:08:36.472
so he could pull one over on us.

151
00:08:36.516 --> 00:08:39.475
Mano Sangriento is all over
Long Island and Manhattan now.

152
00:08:39.519 --> 00:08:41.564
They all use
the black hand. He played us.

153
00:08:41.608 --> 00:08:44.785
I've checked every ship
and airline passenger list.

154
00:08:44.828 --> 00:08:46.003
I don't think he left town.

155
00:08:46.047 --> 00:08:47.439
Look. it's been weeks. okay?

156
00:08:47.483 --> 00:08:49.441
He could be anywhere by
now. including Mexico.

157
00:08:49.485 --> 00:08:51.095
Just speak to the DEA.

158
00:08:51.139 --> 00:08:52.682
See if they'll give you
anything they got on him.

159
00:08:52.706 --> 00:08:54.858
I'll check the warrant my sister
gave me on his cell phone

160
00:08:54.882 --> 00:08:57.232
and see if that
turns anything up.

161
00:09:04.587 --> 00:09:07.459
I think someone else
should find Delgado.

162
00:09:07.503 --> 00:09:09.200
It's way too personal

163
00:09:09.244 --> 00:09:11.246
between you and him. I'm not gonna go

164
00:09:11.289 --> 00:09:13.050
off the rails. if that's
what you're thinking. okay?

165
00:09:13.074 --> 00:09:14.031
I promise.

166
00:09:14.075 --> 00:09:15.293
You already did.

167
00:09:15.337 --> 00:09:17.141
Do you really want to put us
in the crosshairs?

168
00:09:17.165 --> 00:09:18.316
Look. I'm gonna get
that son of a bitch.

169
00:09:18.340 --> 00:09:19.863
no matter what it takes.

170
00:09:22.649 --> 00:09:24.476
You don't want
to be a part of that.

171
00:09:24.520 --> 00:09:27.044
then I suggest
you walk away on this one.

172
00:09:27.088 --> 00:09:29.394
You really want me to walk away?

173
00:09:48.544 --> 00:09:50.328
Mom.

174
00:09:50.372 --> 00:09:51.808
Hi.

175
00:09:51.852 --> 00:09:54.332
Hi.

176
00:09:54.376 --> 00:09:56.247
This is Jamie.

177
00:09:57.553 --> 00:09:59.903
Hi.You didn't tell me
you were bringing someone.

178
00:09:59.947 --> 00:10:01.992
I know. I'm sorry. Jamie Reagan.
Nice to meet you.

179
00:10:02.036 --> 00:10:03.211
How do you do?

180
00:10:03.254 --> 00:10:04.255
Very well.

181
00:10:05.692 --> 00:10:07.258
You're welcome.

182
00:10:07.302 --> 00:10:08.433
Um... Can I steal this?

183
00:10:08.477 --> 00:10:09.870
Yes. no problem.

184
00:10:14.744 --> 00:10:17.573
So...

185
00:10:17.617 --> 00:10:18.966
are you dating?

186
00:10:19.009 --> 00:10:21.446
Is this. like. a new boyfriend?

187
00:10:21.490 --> 00:10:23.710
He-he's my fiancé.

188
00:10:23.753 --> 00:10:26.843
Fiancé?

189
00:10:26.887 --> 00:10:28.932
And this is the first time
I'm meeting you?

190
00:10:28.976 --> 00:10:30.760
Well. we didn't really datedate.

191
00:10:30.804 --> 00:10:31.979
You didn't date?

192
00:10:32.022 --> 00:10:33.130
What he means
is we've known each other

193
00:10:33.154 --> 00:10:34.546
for a long time.

194
00:10:34.590 --> 00:10:36.157
We were partners on the job.

195
00:10:36.200 --> 00:10:38.942
So you're a cop.

196
00:10:38.986 --> 00:10:40.074
He's a sergeant.

197
00:10:43.599 --> 00:10:45.122
He went to Harvard.

198
00:10:45.166 --> 00:10:48.517
A quarter of a million dollars
in tuition

199
00:10:48.560 --> 00:10:50.562
and you decided to be a cop.

200
00:10:50.606 --> 00:10:51.520
Well. my whole family's
in law enforcement.

201
00:10:51.563 --> 00:10:53.478
so I guess it was in the blood.

202
00:10:53.522 --> 00:10:55.611
It's too bad doctor or lawyer
wasn't in the blood.

203
00:10:55.655 --> 00:10:56.743
Then you two could

204
00:10:56.786 --> 00:10:59.615
actually afford
a nice lifestyle.

205
00:10:59.659 --> 00:11:01.443
We love our lifestyle. Mom.

206
00:11:01.486 --> 00:11:02.444
Do you own a house?

207
00:11:02.487 --> 00:11:04.228
I have an apartment.

208
00:11:04.272 --> 00:11:05.534
Eddie likes being in the city.

209
00:11:05.577 --> 00:11:07.841
"Eddie"? No one calls me
Edit. Mom.

210
00:11:07.884 --> 00:11:10.495
I do. Your father does.

211
00:11:10.539 --> 00:11:12.889
Well. I like Eddie.

212
00:11:12.933 --> 00:11:15.587
So. you use a boy's name
and he uses a girl's name.

213
00:11:15.631 --> 00:11:16.458
Mom.

214
00:11:16.501 --> 00:11:18.460
I'm just saying.

215
00:11:18.503 --> 00:11:20.505
That's okay.
My real name's Jameson.

216
00:11:20.549 --> 00:11:21.768
Like the whiskey.

217
00:11:21.811 --> 00:11:23.683
Yeah. like the whiskey.

218
00:11:23.726 --> 00:11:26.250
It's a good thing your parents
didn't like to drink Smirnoff.

219
00:11:26.294 --> 00:11:28.775
Mom. What?

220
00:11:31.168 --> 00:11:34.563
So. Reagan. is that. is that
any relation to...

221
00:11:34.606 --> 00:11:36.246
The police commissioner.
yes. he's my dad.

222
00:11:38.262 --> 00:11:39.437
What?

223
00:11:39.481 --> 00:11:41.570
You must see the humor
in this. Edit.

224
00:11:41.613 --> 00:11:43.093
Your father's in jail.

225
00:11:43.137 --> 00:11:46.270
and you're marrying
the police commissioner's son.

226
00:11:47.707 --> 00:11:50.666
That's going to make for some
very interesting conversation

227
00:11:50.710 --> 00:11:52.799
at the wedding reception.
don't you think?

228
00:11:59.631 --> 00:12:03.287
Looks like Davis has permanent
nerve damage to his hand.

229
00:12:04.288 --> 00:12:06.073
His shooting hand.

230
00:12:06.116 --> 00:12:09.337
so he'll be off
the street for good. Well. not necessarily.

231
00:12:09.380 --> 00:12:12.470
Not with the kind of things
they can do today.

232
00:12:12.514 --> 00:12:14.603
And Brian Baker?

233
00:12:15.647 --> 00:12:17.345
Still the same.

234
00:12:17.388 --> 00:12:19.477
A.D.A. Reagan. boss.

235
00:12:23.960 --> 00:12:25.832
Erin.

236
00:12:25.875 --> 00:12:27.311
Garrett. Sid.

237
00:12:27.355 --> 00:12:29.052
Erin. How's Brian?

238
00:12:29.096 --> 00:12:31.054
Still unconscious.

239
00:12:31.098 --> 00:12:33.796
It's a waiting game right now.

240
00:12:33.840 --> 00:12:36.320
And Abigail?

241
00:12:36.364 --> 00:12:39.019
Abigail hasn't left his side.

242
00:12:42.849 --> 00:12:44.807
Where's your boss?

243
00:12:46.026 --> 00:12:49.116
He's not coming.

244
00:12:51.509 --> 00:12:54.338
Okay.

245
00:12:54.382 --> 00:12:56.906
I'll be in my office. boss.

246
00:13:04.958 --> 00:13:07.308
Cortez was my case.
I supervised it.

247
00:13:07.351 --> 00:13:09.179
It was my responsibility.

248
00:13:09.223 --> 00:13:12.269
What were you thinking
letting him walk?

249
00:13:12.313 --> 00:13:14.445
He didn't walk. He made bail.

250
00:13:14.489 --> 00:13:17.100
Bail was set at 500 bucks. Erin.
Of course he walked.

251
00:13:17.144 --> 00:13:19.407
That's chump change
for a drug dealer.

252
00:13:19.450 --> 00:13:22.976
The arrest was
for a nonviolent drug charge.

253
00:13:23.019 --> 00:13:24.891
We are not in the business
of asking

254
00:13:24.934 --> 00:13:27.763
for high bail because we think
someone mightbecome dangerous.

255
00:13:27.807 --> 00:13:31.723
He has a felony record
in Mexico Murder. assault.

256
00:13:31.767 --> 00:13:34.814
My office didn't have access
to that information.

257
00:13:36.119 --> 00:13:38.121
So the D.A.'s office

258
00:13:38.165 --> 00:13:40.210
is in a rush to hold his hand.

259
00:13:40.254 --> 00:13:43.561
and he goes out
and shoots two of my cops.

260
00:13:44.562 --> 00:13:46.564
What do you want me to say. Dad?

261
00:13:46.608 --> 00:13:50.264
The department policy is to ask
for little or no bail

262
00:13:50.307 --> 00:13:52.005
for nonviolent crimes.

263
00:13:52.048 --> 00:13:54.703
The policy has had success.

264
00:13:55.747 --> 00:13:57.532
Not so much.

265
00:14:20.685 --> 00:14:23.036
Where is he?

266
00:14:23.079 --> 00:14:25.299
I don't know who
you're talking about.

267
00:14:25.342 --> 00:14:26.691
The guy you're standing next to

268
00:14:26.735 --> 00:14:29.390
in the painting over
there. Where is he?

269
00:14:33.785 --> 00:14:34.743
No...

270
00:14:34.786 --> 00:14:37.006
Don't even think about it.

271
00:14:37.050 --> 00:14:38.355
You're trespassing.

272
00:14:38.399 --> 00:14:39.704
You broke into myhouse.

273
00:14:39.748 --> 00:14:42.359
You mean like
your husband trespassed

274
00:14:42.403 --> 00:14:44.622
when he burned my house down?

275
00:14:44.666 --> 00:14:46.494
Mom?

276
00:14:47.408 --> 00:14:48.408
Is everything okay?

277
00:14:50.454 --> 00:14:52.413
Go back inside.

278
00:14:54.632 --> 00:14:56.417
Where's your phone? In the kitchen.

279
00:14:56.460 --> 00:14:57.897
Let's go get it.

280
00:15:00.464 --> 00:15:02.771
Your husband's making a lot
of money terrorizing people.

281
00:15:02.814 --> 00:15:04.381
Who's terrorizing who?

282
00:15:04.425 --> 00:15:05.992
Get the phone. Pick it up.

283
00:15:06.035 --> 00:15:07.994
Call your husband. Come on.

284
00:15:08.037 --> 00:15:09.865
Turn around.

285
00:15:09.909 --> 00:15:12.476
Don't do anything crazy.

286
00:15:16.045 --> 00:15:17.786
Luis?

287
00:15:19.135 --> 00:15:20.615
Hey. remember me?

288
00:15:20.658 --> 00:15:22.530
Where's Isabel? She's right here.

289
00:15:22.573 --> 00:15:24.464
Kids are here. too.
But don't worry. they're safe.

290
00:15:24.488 --> 00:15:26.379
Unless. of course.
I decide to burn your house down

291
00:15:26.403 --> 00:15:27.839
like you burned down mine.

292
00:15:27.883 --> 00:15:29.189
If you harm them.

293
00:15:29.232 --> 00:15:32.366
I swear I'll kill you.

294
00:15:32.409 --> 00:15:34.977
Well. then you better
hurry up and get home.

295
00:15:35.021 --> 00:15:36.283
Sit down.

296
00:15:47.947 --> 00:15:50.036
Officer Davis took a bullet
to his right hand.

297
00:15:50.079 --> 00:15:52.038
which has caused
permanent nerve damage.

298
00:15:52.081 --> 00:15:54.779
Officer Baker was hit
with a bullet in his neck.

299
00:15:54.823 --> 00:15:57.869
which punctured his jugular.

300
00:15:57.913 --> 00:16:02.526
The bullet was removed. but he
has not regained consciousness.

301
00:16:02.570 --> 00:16:04.964
We will have updates
as things progress.

302
00:16:06.226 --> 00:16:07.575
What about the shooter?

303
00:16:07.618 --> 00:16:09.011
The shooter. Jose Cortez.

304
00:16:09.055 --> 00:16:11.361
was apprehended
shortly after the shooting.

305
00:16:11.405 --> 00:16:13.015
He has been charged

306
00:16:13.059 --> 00:16:14.669
with attempted murder
in the first degree

307
00:16:14.712 --> 00:16:16.932
and will be arraigned
later this afternoon.

308
00:16:16.976 --> 00:16:19.041
Initial reports said Cortez
had been arrested before.

309
00:16:19.065 --> 00:16:20.980
but released on bail. That's correct.

310
00:16:21.023 --> 00:16:23.025
He was arrested for
drug possession

311
00:16:23.069 --> 00:16:24.896
and released on bail
this morning.

312
00:16:24.940 --> 00:16:26.986
Why was he released on bail?

313
00:16:27.029 --> 00:16:28.267
The nonviolent nature
of his crimes

314
00:16:28.291 --> 00:16:30.337
and the lack
of prior criminal history.

315
00:16:30.380 --> 00:16:33.055
Why was he released in the first place?
He was a member of Mano Sangriento.

316
00:16:33.079 --> 00:16:35.081
Mr. Cortez had
no criminal history

317
00:16:35.124 --> 00:16:37.387
or gang affiliation on record.

318
00:16:37.431 --> 00:16:38.998
It was handled

319
00:16:39.041 --> 00:16:40.042
as a first-time offense.

320
00:16:40.086 --> 00:16:41.739
What do you mean. "on record"?

321
00:16:41.783 --> 00:16:44.307
Mr. Cortez had
a prior record in Mexico

322
00:16:44.351 --> 00:16:48.050
that did not come up
on the initial background check.

323
00:16:48.094 --> 00:16:50.052
In light of what happened.
is the D.A.'s office

324
00:16:50.096 --> 00:16:51.619
going to rethink this policy?

325
00:16:51.662 --> 00:16:55.753
The policy was established
to decrease overcrowded prisons

326
00:16:55.797 --> 00:16:57.320
filled with
nonviolent offenders.

327
00:16:57.364 --> 00:17:01.063
In this regard.
the policy is a success.

328
00:17:01.107 --> 00:17:04.153
The NYPD has two good officers
in the hospital.

329
00:17:04.197 --> 00:17:06.416
one facing disability.

330
00:17:06.460 --> 00:17:08.723
one may not survive.

331
00:17:08.766 --> 00:17:11.073
Asking for minimum bail

332
00:17:11.117 --> 00:17:13.423
for felonies puts my officers

333
00:17:13.467 --> 00:17:15.164
and. more importantly.

334
00:17:15.208 --> 00:17:16.948
our citizens at risk.

335
00:17:16.992 --> 00:17:20.082
because these criminals
will then be incentivized

336
00:17:20.126 --> 00:17:22.215
to go out and commit more.

337
00:17:22.258 --> 00:17:24.086
worse crimes.

338
00:17:24.130 --> 00:17:26.175
And that is exactly
what happened today.

339
00:17:28.047 --> 00:17:29.831
That's all.

340
00:17:29.874 --> 00:17:31.114
Thank you. Thank you very much.

341
00:17:38.144 --> 00:17:39.251
I don't know how you
actually thought

342
00:17:39.275 --> 00:17:40.600
you could avoid me
meeting your mother.

343
00:17:40.624 --> 00:17:43.018
I was doing a great job
avoiding until today.

344
00:17:43.062 --> 00:17:44.822
Eddie. you've met my whole
family; They're not perfect.

345
00:17:44.846 --> 00:17:47.544
You have... you know. you have
a Norman Rockwell family.

346
00:17:47.588 --> 00:17:49.783
You go to church on Sundays.
and you eat together on Sundays.

347
00:17:49.807 --> 00:17:51.461
Just please don't.

348
00:17:51.505 --> 00:17:53.550
Just saying. it doesn't
bother me what she says.

349
00:17:53.594 --> 00:17:56.205
She just has no filter.

350
00:17:56.249 --> 00:17:57.511
And she only cares

351
00:17:57.554 --> 00:17:59.165
about money.

352
00:17:59.208 --> 00:18:01.143
Eddie. do you know why we have
family dinner every Sunday?

353
00:18:01.167 --> 00:18:02.777
No. Why?

354
00:18:02.820 --> 00:18:05.693
Because my grandmother grew up
poor in a small town in Ireland.

355
00:18:05.736 --> 00:18:07.216
She was the oldest of 12 kids.

356
00:18:07.260 --> 00:18:09.131
and there was never
enough to eat.

357
00:18:09.175 --> 00:18:11.133
She moved to New York
to make money.

358
00:18:11.177 --> 00:18:13.135
She met my grandpa. and
when they got married.

359
00:18:13.179 --> 00:18:14.876
she promised herself
that they would always

360
00:18:14.919 --> 00:18:16.617
have more than enough to eat.

361
00:18:16.660 --> 00:18:18.227
Family dinner was

362
00:18:18.271 --> 00:18:21.100
just her way of proudly
proving that every week.

363
00:18:22.623 --> 00:18:27.454
That meal was so important to
her because of how she grew up.

364
00:18:27.497 --> 00:18:29.934
I'm just saying. there must be
some deep-seated reason

365
00:18:29.978 --> 00:18:32.067
why your mother is
so obsessed about money.

366
00:18:32.111 --> 00:18:35.810
My mother choosesto insult me

367
00:18:35.853 --> 00:18:39.205
and to insult every person
I've ever brought home.

368
00:18:55.830 --> 00:18:57.832
Yeah. Leave the car there

369
00:18:57.875 --> 00:18:59.268
and walk to the garage.

370
00:19:12.107 --> 00:19:13.239
Welcome home.

371
00:19:13.282 --> 00:19:14.849
Come on in.

372
00:19:15.893 --> 00:19:17.721
Right over there.

373
00:19:21.769 --> 00:19:23.249
Keep your hands where

374
00:19:23.292 --> 00:19:25.381
I can see 'em. Where's my wife and my boys?

375
00:19:25.425 --> 00:19:28.558
Why'd you set my house on fire?

376
00:19:28.602 --> 00:19:30.145
You're really pretending
to be an innocent victim?

377
00:19:30.169 --> 00:19:32.475
Who gave you the order? Doesn't matter.

378
00:19:32.519 --> 00:19:34.390
You think if you
take him down. it's over?

379
00:19:34.434 --> 00:19:36.262
You guys thought
you got El Chapo.

380
00:19:36.305 --> 00:19:38.307
There's 20 guys lining up
to be the next El Chapo.

381
00:19:38.351 --> 00:19:40.179
That's how
these organizations work.

382
00:19:40.222 --> 00:19:43.225
How this works is that I'm
gonna find every son of a bitch

383
00:19:43.269 --> 00:19:45.314
who had a hand in setting
my house on fire.

384
00:19:45.358 --> 00:19:47.640
and I'm not gonna stop until
every one of them's behind bars.

385
00:19:47.664 --> 00:19:49.144
or worse.

386
00:19:49.188 --> 00:19:50.711
That's how it works.

387
00:19:50.754 --> 00:19:52.408
Won't bring your wife back.

388
00:19:54.323 --> 00:19:55.977
You have two sons.

389
00:19:56.020 --> 00:19:59.198
You really want
to put them in danger?

390
00:20:02.201 --> 00:20:03.680
Baez. I got Delgado.

391
00:20:03.724 --> 00:20:04.812
Request a 10-85

392
00:20:04.855 --> 00:20:08.119
to 12 Bayview Avenue.

393
00:20:08.163 --> 00:20:09.271
You're under arrest.
Turn around.

394
00:20:09.295 --> 00:20:11.775
Put your hands behind your back.

395
00:20:16.084 --> 00:20:17.781
You made a big mistake.

396
00:20:17.825 --> 00:20:19.914
You're the one making
a mistake. bro.

397
00:20:19.957 --> 00:20:21.394
I'm one of you. Yeah?

398
00:20:21.437 --> 00:20:23.178
How's that?

399
00:20:24.223 --> 00:20:25.876
I'm working for the DEA.

400
00:20:40.326 --> 00:20:42.371
We have you

401
00:20:42.415 --> 00:20:44.330
for the murder
of Melissa Sanchez.

402
00:20:44.373 --> 00:20:46.201
No. you don't.DANNY Yes. we do.

403
00:20:46.245 --> 00:20:48.334
You told me you killed her
and her unborn baby.

404
00:20:48.377 --> 00:20:50.336
I told you
I didn't think she was okay.

405
00:20:50.379 --> 00:20:52.381
As it turns out. I was right.

406
00:20:52.425 --> 00:20:55.341
She wasn't okay. She was dead.

407
00:20:56.342 --> 00:20:58.692
And Manny Sanchez.

408
00:21:00.520 --> 00:21:02.348
Reagan. what do you think
you're doing?

409
00:21:02.391 --> 00:21:04.219
What the hell do you think
you'redoing?

410
00:21:04.263 --> 00:21:05.612
Can I talk to you outside?

411
00:21:13.141 --> 00:21:14.379
What the hell are you doing
here? And more importantly.

412
00:21:14.403 --> 00:21:15.230
what the hell
are you doing working

413
00:21:15.274 --> 00:21:17.145
with a scumbag like Delgado?

414
00:21:17.188 --> 00:21:18.557
We made a deal with him.
Yeah. I know you did.

415
00:21:18.581 --> 00:21:20.322
You made a deal
with a cold-blooded killer

416
00:21:20.366 --> 00:21:22.759
who murdered an innocent woman
and her unborn baby.

417
00:21:22.803 --> 00:21:26.023
Delgado's a hired hand.
We're after José Rojas.

418
00:21:26.067 --> 00:21:28.330
His boss. La Almeja. The Clam.

419
00:21:28.374 --> 00:21:30.506
Okay. Delgado is a hired gun.

420
00:21:30.550 --> 00:21:34.902
Rojas has murdered or ordered
the murder of hundreds.

421
00:21:34.945 --> 00:21:37.861
Okay? We get Rojas.
we bring down the organization.

422
00:21:37.905 --> 00:21:39.298
Great. then go get him.

423
00:21:39.341 --> 00:21:41.125
I already got Delgado.
He's mine.

424
00:21:41.169 --> 00:21:43.302
No. you're gonna back off.

425
00:21:43.345 --> 00:21:44.738
Go to hell.

426
00:21:44.781 --> 00:21:47.741
Look. I get that this
has gotten personal for you.

427
00:21:47.784 --> 00:21:49.371
Don't go there. Okay. but we don't need you

428
00:21:49.395 --> 00:21:52.572
going in there. being a hothead.
blowing our case.

429
00:21:52.615 --> 00:21:55.009
I arrested Delgado.
It's my collar.

430
00:21:55.052 --> 00:21:57.422
Are you kidding me right now? I
got him on murder charges. Okay?

431
00:21:57.446 --> 00:21:59.883
That trumps any drug charge
you could possibly get.

432
00:21:59.927 --> 00:22:01.798
So unless you want
to go before a judge

433
00:22:01.842 --> 00:22:03.583
and try to get him
to give you a writ for me

434
00:22:03.626 --> 00:22:05.387
to turn him over to the feds.
so be it. You go do that.

435
00:22:05.411 --> 00:22:07.717
But until such time.
Delgado's mine.

436
00:22:07.761 --> 00:22:09.153
He stays here with me.

437
00:22:09.197 --> 00:22:11.199
Hey.

438
00:22:12.809 --> 00:22:14.245
What?

439
00:22:14.289 --> 00:22:15.986
Maybe we can work together
on this.

440
00:22:17.205 --> 00:22:18.424
Well. it's the only way

441
00:22:18.467 --> 00:22:20.426
we're both gonna get
what we want.

442
00:22:27.737 --> 00:22:29.870
Bless us. O Lord.
and these Thy gifts.

443
00:22:29.913 --> 00:22:32.046
which we are about to receive
from Thy bounty.

444
00:22:32.089 --> 00:22:35.179
through Christ our Lord. Amen.

445
00:22:45.842 --> 00:22:49.585
You mind. passing
me the mac and cheese? Sure.

446
00:22:49.629 --> 00:22:51.587
Here you go.

447
00:22:51.631 --> 00:22:52.849
Looks good.

448
00:22:54.460 --> 00:22:55.698
And what's the matter
with Daniel?

449
00:22:55.722 --> 00:22:57.854
Nothing.

450
00:22:57.898 --> 00:22:59.726
Well. you're not piling food
onto your plate.

451
00:22:59.769 --> 00:23:01.205
so it must be something.

452
00:23:01.249 --> 00:23:02.685
Well. I kind of lost my appetite

453
00:23:02.729 --> 00:23:04.707
when I learned that the guy
who burned our house down

454
00:23:04.731 --> 00:23:06.689
cut a deal with the DEA.

455
00:23:06.733 --> 00:23:08.691
You know who burned
our house down?

456
00:23:08.735 --> 00:23:11.259
Yeah. We'll talk about it later.

457
00:23:11.302 --> 00:23:14.697
In the meantime. that guy's
walking around free as a bird.

458
00:23:14.741 --> 00:23:16.873
Well. you could always
blame the D.A.'s office.

459
00:23:16.917 --> 00:23:19.702
It seems to be the common
dumping ground around here.

460
00:23:19.746 --> 00:23:21.965
No one's dumping

461
00:23:22.009 --> 00:23:23.532
on the D.A.'s office.

462
00:23:23.576 --> 00:23:24.707
You saw

463
00:23:24.751 --> 00:23:26.187
the joint press conference.

464
00:23:26.230 --> 00:23:28.276
System's broken.
Somebody had to call it out.

465
00:23:28.319 --> 00:23:29.886
And here I thought
a press conference

466
00:23:29.930 --> 00:23:31.322
was for dispensing information.

467
00:23:31.366 --> 00:23:33.934
not calling people out.
My mistake.

468
00:23:33.977 --> 00:23:36.197
Well. last I heard.
you commit a crime.

469
00:23:36.240 --> 00:23:38.591
you suffer the consequences.
end of story.

470
00:23:38.634 --> 00:23:40.810
You know how many times
you and Jamie have come to me

471
00:23:40.854 --> 00:23:42.856
for a search warrant
or a subpoena.

472
00:23:42.899 --> 00:23:44.814
and you haven't had everything
to get it?

473
00:23:44.858 --> 00:23:45.859
Yeah. about as many times

474
00:23:45.902 --> 00:23:47.426
as you've said no.

475
00:23:47.469 --> 00:23:49.079
I'm sorry.
I still don't understand.

476
00:23:49.123 --> 00:23:50.777
If you know who burned
our house down.

477
00:23:50.820 --> 00:23:52.692
then why is he still walking?

478
00:23:52.735 --> 00:23:55.085
It's something called
judicial perversion.

479
00:23:55.129 --> 00:23:56.435
Judicial diversion.

480
00:23:56.478 --> 00:23:57.784
It's a policy

481
00:23:57.827 --> 00:24:00.787
where nonviolent offenders
get reduced bail

482
00:24:00.830 --> 00:24:04.138
and rehab. community service
instead of jail time.

483
00:24:04.181 --> 00:24:06.836
It's called
mollycoddling criminals.

484
00:24:06.880 --> 00:24:08.229
Is there anything

485
00:24:08.272 --> 00:24:10.231
that you guys don't blame
on the attorneys?

486
00:24:10.274 --> 00:24:11.711
Well. I'm afraid at the moment.

487
00:24:11.754 --> 00:24:13.539
there happens
to be plenty to blame.

488
00:24:13.582 --> 00:24:14.583
Amen to that.

489
00:24:14.627 --> 00:24:15.889
That's what you get for having

490
00:24:15.932 --> 00:24:18.587
a liberal D.A.
and a liberal mayor.

491
00:24:18.631 --> 00:24:20.241
Like cops don't make mistakes?

492
00:24:20.284 --> 00:24:22.635
Nobody's saying that.

493
00:24:22.678 --> 00:24:24.090
To be fair. I understand
why he got a reduced bail.

494
00:24:24.114 --> 00:24:26.595
His arrest wasn't
for a large felony weight.

495
00:24:26.639 --> 00:24:28.815
Well. how about his affiliation
with an illegal gang?

496
00:24:28.858 --> 00:24:31.339
Or his criminal record
in Mexico?

497
00:24:31.382 --> 00:24:32.819
His criminal record in Mexico

498
00:24:32.862 --> 00:24:34.951
doesn't come up in
a background check.

499
00:24:34.995 --> 00:24:36.320
It would if you ran him
through Interpol.

500
00:24:36.344 --> 00:24:38.302
Why would I run
a low-level drug dealer

501
00:24:38.346 --> 00:24:39.347
through Interpol?

502
00:24:39.390 --> 00:24:40.479
Why wouldn't you?

503
00:24:44.744 --> 00:24:47.181
You know. when I first started
coming to these family dinners

504
00:24:47.224 --> 00:24:50.576
and you guys would argue.
I would get really nervous

505
00:24:50.619 --> 00:24:53.883
'cause I thought maybe you'd
never talk to each other again.

506
00:24:53.927 --> 00:24:55.842
But...

507
00:24:55.885 --> 00:24:57.365
you do.

508
00:24:57.408 --> 00:25:00.237
You just keep talking.

509
00:25:00.281 --> 00:25:02.936
Come hell or high water.

510
00:25:02.979 --> 00:25:04.590
You saying we talk too much?

511
00:25:04.633 --> 00:25:07.027
No.

512
00:25:07.070 --> 00:25:08.855
Well. don't worry. Eddie.

513
00:25:08.898 --> 00:25:11.858
No matter what you do.
you're golden at this table.

514
00:25:11.901 --> 00:25:13.773
I am?

515
00:25:13.816 --> 00:25:16.602
As long as you wear NYPD blue.

516
00:25:37.057 --> 00:25:38.972
I didn't know
you were coming here.

517
00:25:39.015 --> 00:25:40.364
Edit never called me.

518
00:25:40.408 --> 00:25:42.541
I didn't tell her.

519
00:25:42.584 --> 00:25:44.717
May I come in?

520
00:25:50.070 --> 00:25:52.072
I bet she's mad at me.

521
00:25:52.115 --> 00:25:53.377
Well. why wouldn't she be?

522
00:25:53.421 --> 00:25:54.901
She came to give you
some good news.

523
00:25:54.944 --> 00:25:56.337
and you rained on her parade.

524
00:25:56.380 --> 00:25:58.861
The good news would've been
she's marrying someone

525
00:25:58.905 --> 00:26:01.951
who could afford to give her
the life that she's used to.

526
00:26:01.995 --> 00:26:03.213
And what life would that be?

527
00:26:03.257 --> 00:26:05.912
One where your husband's
in prison for fraud

528
00:26:05.955 --> 00:26:07.740
and she wants to cut you
out of her life?

529
00:26:07.783 --> 00:26:09.568
She should be grateful.

530
00:26:09.611 --> 00:26:11.265
We gave her everything.

531
00:26:11.308 --> 00:26:14.007
Your husband cheated people
out of their savings.

532
00:26:14.050 --> 00:26:17.053
You insulted every guy
she ever brought around.

533
00:26:17.097 --> 00:26:18.707
I tell the truth.

534
00:26:18.751 --> 00:26:20.231
And the truth about me
is I don't make

535
00:26:20.274 --> 00:26:22.189
enough money? I'm
the wrong religion?

536
00:26:22.232 --> 00:26:23.340
I live in the wrong borough?

537
00:26:23.364 --> 00:26:24.583
I won't apologize

538
00:26:24.626 --> 00:26:26.236
for wanting what's best
for my daughter.

539
00:26:26.280 --> 00:26:28.804
I'm what's best
for your daughter. Because you love her?

540
00:26:28.848 --> 00:26:31.415
And that's gonna
take care of the bills?

541
00:26:31.459 --> 00:26:34.593
I live a comfortable life.
and my family will. too.

542
00:26:34.636 --> 00:26:37.030
Will it meet your standards?
I don't know.

543
00:26:37.073 --> 00:26:39.336
But my family
will always come first.

544
00:26:39.380 --> 00:26:41.948
That sounds great
on a Hallmark card.

545
00:26:41.991 --> 00:26:43.993
But in reality?

546
00:26:45.734 --> 00:26:47.693
Not so much.

547
00:26:49.042 --> 00:26:52.393
I don't want Edit to end up...

548
00:26:52.436 --> 00:26:53.829
Like you did?

549
00:26:55.788 --> 00:26:56.852
Maybe you need to see the world

550
00:26:56.876 --> 00:26:58.486
through a different set
of glasses.

551
00:26:58.529 --> 00:27:01.968
Well. I certainly don't trust
the rose-colored ones you wear.

552
00:27:02.011 --> 00:27:04.405
You haven't tried them on yet.

553
00:27:14.328 --> 00:27:16.678
I'm in the middle
of pretrial hearings. Pop.

554
00:27:17.723 --> 00:27:20.551
You call me out here for this.

555
00:27:20.595 --> 00:27:23.032
I made you your
favorite sandwich.

556
00:27:23.076 --> 00:27:26.122
Thank you. Now.
what are we doing out here?

557
00:27:26.166 --> 00:27:27.558
Getting you out of the office.

558
00:27:27.602 --> 00:27:30.126
My office is not
the problem. Dad is.

559
00:27:30.170 --> 00:27:32.694
Is he. now? Why?

560
00:27:32.738 --> 00:27:34.478
'Cause he says what he feels?

561
00:27:34.522 --> 00:27:36.959
In front of millions of viewers

562
00:27:37.003 --> 00:27:39.005
at my first press conference
as bureau chief?

563
00:27:39.048 --> 00:27:40.702
Yeah. he could've
tempered it down.

564
00:27:40.746 --> 00:27:42.486
You mean watered it down?

565
00:27:42.530 --> 00:27:44.010
Whatever you want to call it.

566
00:27:44.053 --> 00:27:45.707
You're upset because

567
00:27:45.751 --> 00:27:48.014
he talked like the
police commissioner

568
00:27:48.057 --> 00:27:49.537
and not your father.

569
00:27:49.580 --> 00:27:52.322
I don't see how he could've
handled it any other way.

570
00:27:52.366 --> 00:27:54.150
Of course you're gonna
take his side.

571
00:27:54.194 --> 00:27:55.891
I'm not taking sides.

572
00:27:55.935 --> 00:27:58.981
Why are you taking this
so personally?

573
00:28:01.027 --> 00:28:03.986
I can take the slings and arrows
from other attorneys

574
00:28:04.030 --> 00:28:05.988
and the D.A.
and even the press. but...

575
00:28:06.032 --> 00:28:07.381
But not your father?

576
00:28:07.424 --> 00:28:09.165
He was criticizing

577
00:28:09.209 --> 00:28:12.212
the D.A.'s office. not you.

578
00:28:12.255 --> 00:28:13.406
That's not what it felt like.

579
00:28:13.430 --> 00:28:15.781
and I was the one up there
taking the heat.

580
00:28:15.824 --> 00:28:18.174
You're confusing work
and family.

581
00:28:18.218 --> 00:28:20.437
Your father

582
00:28:20.481 --> 00:28:23.614
has the right to disagree
with the D.A...

583
00:28:23.658 --> 00:28:25.312
Yes. in public.

584
00:28:25.355 --> 00:28:28.968
and yes. even with you
standing there next to him...

585
00:28:29.011 --> 00:28:32.101
Because it's his job.

586
00:28:32.145 --> 00:28:35.191
But no matter what happens.

587
00:28:35.235 --> 00:28:38.673
you'll always have his love
and support.

588
00:28:44.200 --> 00:28:46.637
Every time you leave the house.
you have to call first

589
00:28:46.681 --> 00:28:48.030
to say where you're going.

590
00:28:48.074 --> 00:28:49.225
If you're gonna be late
getting back

591
00:28:49.249 --> 00:28:50.467
or your train is delayed.

592
