your car breaks down.
you need to call us

593
00:28:52.252 --> 00:28:53.688
with the details.

594
00:28:53.732 --> 00:28:56.212
Then I should tell you
the coke and fentanyl exchange

595
00:28:56.256 --> 00:28:57.736
may be going down tonight.

596
00:28:57.779 --> 00:28:59.191
"Maybe going down tonight"? I'll get a call

597
00:28:59.215 --> 00:29:00.913
this afternoon to confirm.

598
00:29:00.956 --> 00:29:02.044
Where?

599
00:29:02.088 --> 00:29:03.045
The old candy factory.

600
00:29:03.089 --> 00:29:05.134
I don't know how many people.

601
00:29:05.178 --> 00:29:07.789
Usually six or seven total.
Members of the Double Treys.

602
00:29:07.833 --> 00:29:10.226
Mano Sangriento. me.

603
00:29:10.270 --> 00:29:11.595
Good. Now we know
where it's going down.

604
00:29:11.619 --> 00:29:13.752
So we don't need him to do this.

605
00:29:13.795 --> 00:29:16.189
Rojas expects me to be
there to handle the money.

606
00:29:16.232 --> 00:29:19.148
If he finds out I'm not.
he'll be in the wind.

607
00:29:19.192 --> 00:29:20.236
Don't trust him.

608
00:29:22.369 --> 00:29:24.763
Wipe that smile off your face.

609
00:29:24.806 --> 00:29:26.886
That's hard to do 'cause
you're so damn entertaining.

610
00:29:28.114 --> 00:29:29.274
Danny. Danny. Reagan! Reagan!

611
00:29:30.333 --> 00:29:31.508
Outside.

612
00:29:33.162 --> 00:29:35.556
Now!

613
00:29:35.599 --> 00:29:37.558
This is too personal for you

614
00:29:37.601 --> 00:29:40.082
and you cannot handle this...
It's not personal.

615
00:29:40.126 --> 00:29:42.128
I don't trust the son
of a bitch. okay?

616
00:29:42.171 --> 00:29:44.043
Well. we're on it.

617
00:29:44.086 --> 00:29:46.132
You don't know how
that guy works. No?

618
00:29:46.175 --> 00:29:49.048
35 years ago.
my father crossed the border

619
00:29:49.091 --> 00:29:51.093
to get away
from Mano Sangriento.

620
00:29:51.137 --> 00:29:53.400
Okay. when he finally had
enough money.

621
00:29:53.443 --> 00:29:56.316
he went back to get the rest
of his family.

622
00:29:56.359 --> 00:30:00.146
Sangriento had killed
every last one of them.

623
00:30:00.189 --> 00:30:02.539
So...

624
00:30:02.583 --> 00:30:04.237
don't tell me I don't know him.

625
00:30:04.280 --> 00:30:06.282
Look. I'm sorry.

626
00:30:06.326 --> 00:30:08.328
I am.

627
00:30:09.764 --> 00:30:11.611
But you're playing with fire.
trusting this guy.

628
00:30:11.635 --> 00:30:13.202
You're the one playing
with fire.

629
